Malaysia Corruption Officers Suspended After Death, Times Says

-- B y   C h o n g   P o o i   K o o n
-- 
2011-04-08T02:31:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-08/malaysia-corruption-officers-suspended-after-death-times-says.html
The Malaysian Anti-Corruption
Commission suspended two officers after a customs executive
being investigated for graft was found dead at the agency’s
office this week, the New Straits Times reported, citing
a statement from the commission.  They had allegedly breached standard operating procedure
when they failed to be with the witness at all times while on
the agency’s premises, the report said.  Click here for web link  To contact the reporter on this story:
